types of actions that we would literally die of starvation and other things.  Generalizations are a must to survive.  However, whenever making generalizations, our bodies also recognize that there *could* be a difference in a generalized group.  For instance, the first or last step of a flight of stairs could be longer or shorter than the rest, so generalizing always has to be committed with the understanding that the &quot;general&quot; information is not always true.<br>
<br>
What counts as racist?  Well, if you live in a ghetto where almost all the crime is committed by blacks, and the ratio of crimes to race is much more substantial to the black race, then it is NOT racist to believe that black people in that area *in general* are more dangerous than white people.  It is NOT racist to be more afraid of seeing a group of black men walking down the street at night than if you saw a group of white men.  Statistical facts cannot be racist, they are only truth.  This is called being a realist.  Now, by no means am I suggesting that all black people are bad people etc etc, and I know for a fact I am not racist (I have friends of many kinds of races and some are black).  In fact, my black friends even agree to this.  They totally understand.  They don't like it and they wish that such problems could be solved, but even they are more afraid of black men at night then white men.  Being racist, in some sense, means you have to be willing to ignore the exceptions to what you previously thought.  It means to deny the chance of changing that generalization.  It means to believe that such characteristics are innate in all people of that race and there is nothing to change that.  <br>
<br>
Anyways, I haven't read the thread where someone called Cale racist, perhaps I could get a post or something.  I'd like to hear the argument about him being a racist though, considering the new light of info. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=radgen>Radgen</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/misc_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I read boards more<br>than I play EQ....</span><br>  Posts: 712<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/17/03 12:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=632.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/Radgen5.jpg height=150 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm a racist</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Statistical facts cannot be racist, they are only truth. This is called being a realist. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
