<br>
That's the difference.<br>
<br>
I felt very uncomfortable walking into Wal-Mart about a month ago due to the fact that there were about 10 people, all dressed up like extras from &quot;Menace 2 Society&quot;, grunting at each other and flashing hand gestures while loitering around the entrance.  The fact that they were all black certainly registered on me, but my first thought was, &quot;What a shame that these guys are perpetuating the sort of stereotypes that are all too common... and I sure as hell hope that they don't try to steal my shit when I walk back out.&quot;  That, and I found it hilariously funny... the grunting sounded like something out of a Discovery Channel &quot;Africa Safari&quot; documentary covering the activities of baboons.  **NOTE!!: I am not calling black people baboons.  I am saying that these people (who happened to be black) were making the conscious choice to SOUND like baboons, thus making idiots of themselves**<br>
<br>
It's all about the choices you make, and how they reflect on you... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=count16>count16</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 245<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/03 9:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=632.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm a racist</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Actually I do consider your scenario racist. You mention nothing about the demeanor/attitude of the group of people you see on the street, merely the color of their skin. Now, most likely you didn't mean it this way. Obviously if this group of black men were all dressed up in Calvin Klein suits, you wouldn't act the same way. But even then, I would say that is racist as you are judging them on their appearance and racial generalizations.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
