That is true, because on a topic in which people discuss racism, which is a sensitive issue, its important to draw lines exactly where you want them.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>In other words, I am merely suggesting not to use this example to show you aren't racist. It isn't very persuasive. Also, I think people should really analyze their outlook on other ethnicities because I believe everyone has a little bit of racism/racial profiling in their minds; they just have to admit it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
Alright I have to bite a litte, if by &quot;racism&quot; you STRICTLY mean &quot;categorizing some general attributes to certain races in certain circumstances&quot; then YES you can consider all that I said racist.  If you for one very little split second mention anything about hatred, unwillingness to believe in decency of a race, that that particular race (whatever race it is) has no good attributes, etc etc then NO not by that liberal definition am I or anything I said a racist.  I just want to clarify exactly where I stand, and also what is acceptable in our society.  By &quot;some general attributes givin to certain races&quot; racism IS acceptable in our society.  Wanna know why?  Well, I assume that a black person can take the radiation of the sun a lot better than a white person without obtaining cancer.  THATS RACISM by the definition I gave above, and yet its absolutely true.  Its racist to believe that white people produce more vitamin D in their skin than do black people.  Its racist to believe that Mexicans live in or somewhere down the line came from Mexico.  Its racist to believe that Asian-Americans are pretty smart.  Its footism to believe that feet stink.  Do you see the problems with that definition?  Every single generalization that a person makes is &quot;.....ist&quot; even if its statistically or scientifically true.  This simply means you are anti-generalizationist., which I already clarified that generalizations are necessary to human life to survive, so perhaps that means you are a hypocrit?  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Also, I think people should really analyze their outlook on other ethnicities because I believe everyone has a little bit of racism/racial profiling in their minds; they just have to admit it.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
For me in particular its not about having to admit anything.  I'm fully open about my beliefs in front of anyone and everyone, including myself.  My views aren't racist unless you strictly mean what I said in that whole paragraph above (which is rediculous).  Instead, what I think is that you are very sensitive to the issue to the point where you are racist against yourself and have some sort of lack of dignity.<br>
