<br>
Where it gets grey is in examples like airport security... should Makino be searched, even though she looks nothing like a possible hijacker?  (All the 9/11 hijackers were Arabic...)  Should my grandmother?  Hijackers aren't going to come to the airport wearing an Osama bin-Laden t-shirt like a gangster is going to walk around trying to look tough.  It's a hard decision, with a lot of implications.  On the one hand, I think it's absolutely ridiculous to strip-search that 80 year old lady and Al Gore, just to make the point that you're being &quot;fair&quot;.  On the other, Arabs are not the only potential hijackers...  Entebbe, anyone?  But *most* of them are.  Is taking them aside &quot;racist&quot;, i.e. characterized by the belief that one group of people are inferior to or superior to another?  It's not even the genes we're talking about here - it's not racist to say that black people are more at risk for disease X, different groups of people obviously are different in certain biological ways.  It's saying that this group of people tend toward a certain behavior pattern due to the cultural/educational values that tend to be instilled in them... is that racist?  I think its a hard decision. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.visveres.myguilds.com/sigs/caledhon.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caledhontelrana>Caledhon TelRana</A> at: 4/19/03 9:57:32 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=count16>count16</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>l33t board camper</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/03 10:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=632.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=l