As for what I consider part of the definition of &quot;racism&quot; is that you have some sort of inferiority or superiority concept involved with it.  Keep in mind, after all these years the part of &quot;racism&quot; that has caused problems is the ideology of a race being inferior to another.  Take that part out.  Leave what you have with racism.  It no longer is a negative thing!  Its just simply an opinion this way or that way, or a belief based on what you see in your life.  And since every person's life is different every could be racist in a different way and nobody would get hurt and nobody would be offended by the &quot;you are inferior to me&quot; concept.  Its of my belief that its the stripping of dignity that causes the pain in racism. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/bthetribunaldotorg.showUserPublicProfile?gid=makino>Makino</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Flowers Before Boys</span><br>  Posts: 240<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(4/19/03 11:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fthetribunaldotorgfrm36.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=632.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://roforums.dhs.org/phpBB/images/avatars/gallery/Avatars/mage-female.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm a racist</span><hr size=1> You see, I don't jive with witht his definition of racism as it is not always about superiroity/inferiority.  I'll write more when I'm not drunk out of my mind.  It took me 5 minutes to write just this coherently. <p>&lt;hr&gt;<br>
