Now regarding the physical attributes thing, you are correlating physical attributes to scientific fact, which is very different than passing judgement on people, for good or bad, based upon their ethnicity. The Mexican example is just a lame example. And I have met plenty of dumb Asians heh. Although I have a general theory as to why Asians are perceived above average intelligence. Anyways I have no problem with scientific generlizations. For example, the sun thing. Statistics I have major problems with, as it is very difficult to have unbiased or unflawed surveys, esp when it comes to people. Yet, statistics have a way of influencing a person's opinion. This is very dangerous as these people are now running around with incomplete data in their heads.<br>
